DATA BASE DESIGN:
patients – Stores patient personal info.
doctors – Stores doctor details & specialization.
appointments – Links patients & doctors with date/time, includes reminders.
treatments – Records treatment details for each patient.
prescriptions – Links treatments to prescribed medicines.
LIST OF ALL COLUMS:
1️⃣ patient
patient_id` → INT, Primary Key, Auto Increment
first_name` → VARCHAR(50)
last_name` → VARCHAR(50)
date_of_birth` → DATE
gender` → ENUM('Male', 'Female', 'Other')
phone` → VARCHAR(15)
email` → VARCHAR(100)
address` → TEXT
2️⃣ doctors
doctor_id` → INT, Primary Key, Auto Increment
first_name` → VARCHAR(50)
last_name` → VARCHAR(50)
specialization` → VARCHAR(100)
phone` → VARCHAR(15)
email` → VARCHAR(100)
3️⃣ appointments
appointment_id` → INT, Primary Key, Auto Increment
patient_id` → INT (FK → patients.patient\_id)
doctor_id` → INT (FK → doctors.doctor\_id)
appointment_date` → DATETIME
status` → ENUM('Scheduled', 'Completed', 'Cancelled')
4️⃣ treatments
treatment_id` → INT, Primary Key, Auto Increment
appointment_id` → INT (FK → appointments.appointment\_id)
description` → TEXT
cost` → DECIMAL(10,2)
5️⃣ prescriptions**
prescription_id` → INT, Primary Key, Auto Increment
treatment_id` → INT (FK → treatments.treatment\_id)
medicine_name` → VARCHAR(100)
dosage` → VARCHAR(50)
duration` → VARCHAR(50)
